{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀρετή</b> [ᾰ], ἡ, <br /> <b>goodness, excellence,</b> of any kind, in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] especially of <b>manly</b> qualities, ποδῶν ἀρετὴν ἀναφαίνων[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 20.411; ἀμείνων παντοίας ἀρετὰς ἠμὲν πόδας ἠδὲ μάχεσθαι καὶ νόον 15.642\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; so of the gods, τῶν περ καὶ μείζων ἀ. τιμή τε βίη τε[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 9.498\">Refs</a>]; also of women, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.206\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἀ. εἵνεκα for <b>valour,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.92: _plural_, ἀ. ἀπεδείκνυντο\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] displayed <b>brave deeds,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 1.176, 9.40. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__b</b></Level4> later, of the gods, chiefly in <i>plural</i>, <b>glorious deeds, wonders, miracles</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 1172, 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 17.1.17; ζῶσαι ἀ. “IG” 14.966, cf. NT.1Pet.2.9\">NT+1st c.BC+</a>]: also in <i>singular</i>, ὄψιν ἰδοῦσα ἀρετὴν τῆς θεοῦ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 2.1426 b, compare 3rd c.BC: Isyllus Lyricus 62, “BSA” 21.169,180. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> generally, <b>excellence,</b> ἡ ἀ. τελείωσίς τις[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Metaphysica” 1021b20, compare “EN” 1106a15, etc. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of persons, ἄνδρα πὺξ ἀρετὰν εὑρόντα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 7.89, compare “P.” 4.187, 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus 9.13, etc.; τὸ φρονεῖν ἀ. μεγίστη 1st c.AD(?): Heraclitus 112\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: in <i>plural</i>, <b>forms of excellence,</b> μυρίαι ἀνδρῶν ἀ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus 13.8, compare 5th c.BC: Gorgias Rhetor et Sophista “fragment” 8, etc.; δικαστοῦ αὕτη ἀ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 18a\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; especially <b>moral virtue,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 179, 263, +others, 5th c.BC: Gorgias Rhetor et Sophista “fragment” 6\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to κακία, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 2.1.21, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 500d, “Lg.” 963a, 963cf, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 60.17, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1102a6, “Pol.” 1295a37, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>good nature, kindness,</b> etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 163. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__2.b</b></Level4> of animals, things, as land, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.198, 7.5, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.2\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἡ ἐν ἀρετῇ κειμένη γῆ <b>productive</b> land, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PTeb.” 5.165 (2nd c.BC)\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; ἵππου[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.88\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κυνῶν, ἵππων, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 335b; σκεύους [prev. work] 601d\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; [ἀστακοῦ] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Archestratus Epicus “fragment” 24; ἀ. βίου 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 618c; πολιτείας “Lg.” 886b, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>prosperity,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 13.45. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> ἀ. εἴς τινα <b>active merit, good service</b> done him, ἐς τοὺς Ἕλληνας[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.58, compare 2.40; ἀ. περί τινα 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 1.4.8; ἀνταποδοῦναι ἀ. 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.19; ἀρετὰς παρασχέσθαι ὑπέρ τινος 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 19.312\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀρετῆς ἕνεκα, frequently in honorary Inscrr., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 22.107.14, etc. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>reward</b> of excellence, <b>distinction, fame,</b> πλούτῳ δ᾽ ἀρετὴ καὶ κῦδος ὀπηδεῖ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 313, compare 7th-6th c.BC: Sappho Lyrica 80, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 5.53, +others; ἀθάνατος ἀ. 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 1420, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 208d; ἃ ἆθλα τοῦ πολέμου τοῖς ἀνδράσιν ἐστίν, ἐλευθερία καὶ ἀ. 4th c.BC: Lycurgus Orator 49 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of God, δόξα καὶ ἀ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.2Pet.1.3\">NT</a>]: in <i>plural</i>, <b>glories,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 30, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 10.2, +others; πλοῦτος ἀρεταῖς δεδαιδαλμένος [prev. author] “O.” 2.53; γενναίων ἀ. πόνων 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 357 (Lyric poetry), compare 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 2.26; προγόνων ἀ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 618b; in LXX \">LXX+6th c.BC+</a>] frequently of the <b>praises</b> of God, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Isaeus Orator 42.8, +others \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> Ἀρετή personified, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Prodicus Philosophus 1, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Fragmenta” 675, 3rd c.BC(?): Callixinus Historicus 2, “CIG” “Corpus Inscriptionum Graecarum” “Corpus Inscriptionum Graecarum” 2786, “SIG” 985.10, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__V</b></Level2> ἡ ἀ. σου as a title, Your <b>worship,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PLips. 13 ii 20, etc. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__VI</b></Level2> an <b>engine of war,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Athenaeus Mechanicus 38.11. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__VII</b></Level2> a <b>plaster,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Andromachus Poeta Medicus cited in 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 13.531.\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0703","accentedUnicode":"ἀρετή","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0730","matchingForm":"ἄρρην, ἄρσην","stepTransliteration":"arrēn arsēn","gloss":"male","_zh_tw_Gloss":"男","_es_Gloss":"varón","_zh_Gloss":"男"}],"shortDef":"(moral) goodness, excellence, virtue","mediumDef":"(moral) goodness, excellence, virtue <br /><b>goodness, good quality, excellence</b>, of any kind; <b>a gracious act</b> of God, <ref='1Pe.2.9'>1Pet. 2:9;</ref> <ref='2Pe.1.3'>2Pet. 1:3;</ref> <b>virtue, uprightness,</b> <ref='Php.4.8'>Phil. 4:8;</ref> <ref='2Pe.1.5'>2Pet. 1:5</ref>*","stepGloss":"virtue","stepTransliteration":"aretē","count":5,"_es_Definition":"excelencia moral, bondad ; actos redentores, poder (de Dios)","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 優秀的品性, 過人的美德<br>2) 神蹟 (彼前 2:9; 彼後 1:3)","_zh_Definition":"1) 优秀的品性, 过人的美德<br>2) 神迹 (彼前 2:9; 彼后 1:3)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"sự đức độ; nhân đức ; đức hạnh","_zh_tw_Gloss":"美德","_es_Gloss":"virtud","_zh_Gloss":"美德"}]}